Here, you’ll have the opportunity to learn more about New Dragons, understand how the competitive roster selection works, know what to expect for water season, and more! Additionally, we will also be providing free pizza and pop to anyone who attends! 🍕

SOLD OUT!

Get ready for a spooktacular time at Canada's Wonderland! Join us for a night of thrills and chills at our Halloween Haunt event. Prepare for a night of haunted mazes, scare zones, and live shows.

Why now?

This is a limited-time opportunity to experience Halloween Haunt on the first night of the season! That means...

🔥 Warm Weather
🔥 No Midterms
🔥 Before the Weekend
🔥 You have nothing to lose!

This ticket package includes:

👻 Admission x1 to Canada's Wonderland 👻 Halloween Haunt
👻 Two-way TTC Ticket
👻 Directions to Canada's Wonderland
👻 Emergency Contact(s)

On the day of the event, NCSC will be leaving New College, 45 Willcocks in 30-minute interval cohorts for students requiring transportation assistance.

Timings of the cohorts are as follows (may be subject to change):

🚌 2:30 PM
🚌 3:00 PM
🚌 3:30 PM
🚌 4:00 PM

We highly recommend getting to Wonderland as early as possible to doors open (5:00 PM).

Students are also free to commute on their own.

After purchasing your ticket please come to the NCSC office located in 45 Willcocks (next to the Second Cup) on the following dates and times to pick up your package.

🤡 Monday, September 23rd: 3pm-7pm
🤡 Tuesday, September 24th: 3pm - 7pm
🤡 Wednesday, September 25th: 2pm-7pm
🤡 Thursday, September 26th: 5pm-9pm
🤡 Friday, September 27th: 1:30pm-3pm

You may only pick up your OWN ticket. If the above timings do not work for you, please email president@ncsc.ca to set up an alternative time.

Ticket link: https://www.eventbrite.com/e/ncsc-halloween-haunt-tickets-1022278180557?utm-campaign=social&utm-content=attendeeshare&utm-medium=discovery&utm-term=listing&utm-source=cp&aff=ebdsshcopyurl

🗳️ NAUS Voting is LIVE! 🗳️

It’s time to choose your NAUS execs for the upcoming term! Voting is open from September 21-24, 2024, and it’s all virtual! 💻

Positions to be voted on:

2 Second-Year Representatives
1 VP Communications
1 Secretary
2 Graphic Designers

🔗 Check out the link in our bio to cast your vote! Don’t forget to upload proof of enrollment in a Neuroscience POSt or relevant course to participate. Your votes are greatly appreciated, and every decision shapes our future as a community! 🧠✨

Last but certainly not least, meet Dr. McIntyre! 🎊 Learn more about his world renowned research this afternoon at our Neuropsychiatry Symposium, on September 20th from 4:00-6:30, taking place at the Medical Sciences building, room 3153. 💡💜💙

Introducing Dr. Whissell! 🎊 Learn more about his work in behavioural neuroscience at our Neuropsychiatry Symposium taking place tomorrow, September 20th from 4:00-6:30 PM, at the Medical Sciences Building, room 3153! 💡

Meet Dr. Zrenner! Learn more about his incredible research in neurology at the PSA x NAUS Neuropsychiatry Symposium, taking place September 20th, from 4:00-6:30 at the Medical Sciences Building, room 3153. 🧠💡🎉

🍁 APPLE PICKING SEASON!!

Join Regenisis at our 🍎 picking event this Friday, Sept 27th! We will be commuting together — meet at St.George Station at 9:30AM 🌟

The event is $10 per student and $25 for non-students.  You can sign up here or in the LINK IN BIO: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScEcK3nX6eMTETvgK9cC9Koo8fzN34p6-2M_fee0-C24m6obQ/viewform
